Air France, Areva, Carrefour and Iliad: French Equity Preview

-- B y   L a u r e n c e   F r o s t
-- 
2011-06-13T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-12/air-france-areva-carrefour-and-iliad-french-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose stocks may have unusual changes in Paris. Symbols are in
parentheses after company names and prices are from the last
close.  France’s benchmark  CAC 40 Index (CAC)  fell 1.9 percent to
3,805.09. The broader SBF 120 Index declined 1.8 percent to
2,878.25.  Air France-KLM (AF)  Group: Europe’s biggest airline said
an open-ended strike by ground maintenance staff may disrupt
some flights to and from Paris. The shares fell 1.4 percent to
10.56 euros.  Areva SA (AREVA FP): The French government may name a
successor to  Anne Lauvergeon , who is likely to step down as
chief executive officer of the world’s biggest nuclear plant
builder when her contract expires at the end of June, Le Journal
du Dimanche reported. The shares fell 1.7 percent to 25.22
euros.  Carrefour SA (CA)  : Strike action disrupted business at
350 of the retailer’s 540 French supermarkets in the Carrefour
Market chain, Le Parisien reported, citing unions, while the
company put the figure at 50. The shares fell 1.4 percent to
29.18 euros.  Iliad SA (ILD)  : The broadband services provider may open
France’s fourth mobile-phone network as soon as October, Le
Figaro said. The shares fell 0.2 percent to 88.06 euros.  LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA (MC)  : LVMH’s Sephora
cosmetics brand said it acquired another 20 percent of Russia’s
Ile de Beaute, raising its stake to 65 percent. The shares fell
1.8 percent to 114.80 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laurence Frost in Paris at 
 lfrost4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vidya Root in Paris at   vroot@bloomberg.net  